-- Aflac’s Kirsch Hires Sasaki as Japan Chief Investment Officer
-- B y   Z a c h a r y   T r a c e r
-- 2012-08-07T12:49:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-07/aflac-s-kirsch-hires-sasaki-as-japan-chief-investment-officer.html
Aflac Inc. (AFL) , the largest seller of
supplemental health insurance, hired Issei Sasaki as chief
investment officer of the company’s Japan operation.  Sasaki, who previously worked in Tokyo for Massachusetts
Mutual Life Insurance Co. will report to Tohru Tonoike, the
president of Aflac Japan, and to Eric Kirsch, the chief
investment officer, Columbus, Georgia-based Aflac said in a
statement distributed by PR Newswire.  To contact the reporter on this story:
